<a name="newsitem1021649397,53564,"></a> <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><b><font face="Verdana" size="3" color="#DDDD00">Caution on Binding by Firepots</font><font color="#DDDD00"><br>
      </font>
      </b><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#FFC164"><small>11:29 EST - <a href="mailto:hermana@gameznet.com">Hermana</a></small></font><br>
      <br>Once again casters were given the ability to bind by the Firepots.  For alot of us this is a great help, but it seems there are more bugs to worked out with this idea.  The bind is not taking for some people and it's been suggested you wait for some changes to be made before attempting to change your bind location.  For more information on this, click <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000578.html">here</a>.</font></p>
<a name="newsitem1021649123,10722,"></a> <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><b><font face="Verdana" size="3" color="#DDDD00">Trap Bug</font><font color="#DDDD00"><br>
      </font>
      </b><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#FFC164"><small>11:25 EST - <a href="mailto:hermana@gameznet.com">Hermana</a></small></font><br>
      <br>Apparently there is a Bug with the Traps in Ssra Temple.  They seem to follow people around once they are aggroed.  <br><br><blockquote>"While I think it’s a very funny concept, it wasn’t intentional. We’ll try to nail their little feet to the ground with the next patch."</blockquote><br></font></p>
